SIMPLE: uranic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Uranic
<hw>U*ran"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to the heavens; celestial; astronomical.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>On I know not what telluric or <qex>uranic</qex> principles.</q>
<rj><qau>Carlyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, resembling, or
containing uranium; specifically, designating those compounds in which
uranium has a valence relatively higher than in <xex>uranous</xex>
compounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Uranin</ent>⟦br⟧
